==Middle English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|enm|pounde|pund|punde|powund}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|enm|ang|pund}}, in turn from {{inh|enm|gem-pro|*pundą}}, from {{der|enm|la|pondō}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|enm|/puːnd/|/pund/}}

===Noun===
{{enm-noun|pl=poundes|pl2=pounden|pl3=pound}}

# A measurement for weight, most notably the Tower pound, merchant's pound or pound avoirdupois, or a weight of said measurement.
# A {{l|en|pound}} or other silver coin (including ancient coins), weighing one Tower pound of silver.
# Money or coinage in general, especially a great amount of it.

====Descendants====
* {{desc|en|pound}}
* {{desc|sco|pund|poond}}

