==Translingual==

===Etymology 1===
[[File:UncialA-01.svg|upright=0.2|Approximate form of Greek upper case Α (a, “alpha”) that was the source for both common variants of ''a'']]
Modification of capital {{m-lite|mul|A}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{sense-lite|letter, most languages}} {{IPA-lite|mul|/ɑː/|/a/}}
* {{audio|mul|Open_front_unrounded_vowel.ogg|IPA}}

====Letter====
{{head-lite|mul|letters|upper case|A|langname=Translingual}}

# {{ng-lite|The first letter of the [[Appendix:Latin script|basic modern Latin alphabet]].}}

====Symbol====
{{head-lite|mul|symbols|langname=Translingual}}

# {{ng-lite|Used in the [[International Phonetic Alphabet]] and several romanization systems of non-Latin scripts to represent an [[open]] [[front]] [[unrounded]] [[vowel]].}}

