* {{pedia|open front unrounded vowel}}

===Etymology 2===
Abbreviation of {{m-lite|mul|atto-}}, from {{der-lite|mul|da|atten|t=eighteen}}.

====Symbol====
{{head-lite|mul|symbols|langname=Translingual}}

# [[atto-]], prefix for 10<sup>-18</sup> in the [[International System of Units]].

===Etymology 3===
From {{bor-lite|mul|la|annum}} or {{m-lite|la|annus}}.

====Symbol====
{{head-lite|mul|symbols|langname=Translingual}}

# [[year|Year]] as a unit of time, specifically a [[Julian year]] or 365.25 days.

===Etymology 4===
Abbreviation of [[are]], from {{der-lite|mul|fr|are}}.

====Symbol====
{{head-lite|mul|symbols|langname=Translingual}}

# An [[are]], a unit of area one hundredth of a [[hectare]]; ares.

===Etymology 5===
Abbreviation for [[acceleration]]

