=====See also=====
* {{l-lite|en|an}}

===Etymology 3===
* From {{inh-lite|en|enm|a}}, {{m-lite|enm|o}}, from {{inh-lite|en|ang|a-}}, {{m-lite|ang|an}}, {{m-lite|ang|on}}.
* Unstressed form of ''[[on]]''.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA-lite|en|/ə/}}
* {{rhymes-lite|en|ə|s=1}}

====Preposition====
{{head-lite|en|prepositions|langname=English}}

# ''To do with separation;'' In, into. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{ux-lite|en|Torn '''a''' pieces.}}
# ''To do with time;'' Each, per, in, on, by. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{ux-lite|en|I brush my teeth twice '''a''' day.}}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Hamlet|IV|v|text='''A''' Sundays}}
#* {{quote-web|en|title=UN Study: China, US, Japan Lead World AI Development|url=https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/un-study-china-us-japan-lead-world-ai-development/4769094.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207184548/https://learningenglish.voanews.com/a/un-study-china-us-japan-lead-world-ai-development/4769094.html|archivedate=7 February 2019|work={{w|Voice of America}}|date=3 February 2019|passage=Patent requests for machine learning activities grew on average by 28 percent '''a''' year between 2013 and 2016, the study found.}}
#*:: {{audio|en|Patent requests for machine learning activities grew on average by 28 percent a year between 2013 and 2016, the study found.ogg|Audio (US)}}
# ''To do with status;'' In. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* ''{{w|King James Bible}}'' (II Chronicles 2:18)
#*: To set the people '''a''' worke.
# {{lb|en|archaic}} ''To do with position or direction;'' In, on, at, by, towards, onto. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{ux-lite|en|Stand '''a''' tiptoe.}}
# {{lb|en|archaic}} ''To do with process, with a passive verb;'' In the course of, experiencing. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{quote-song|en|1964|{{w|Bob Dylan}}|{{w|The Times They Are a-Changin'}}|passage=The times, they are '''a'''-changin'.}}
# {{lb|en|archaic}} ''To do with an action, an active verb;'' Engaged in. {{defdate|16th c.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Coriolanus|4|2|text=It was '''a''' doing.}}
#* {{RQ:KJV|Hebrews|11|21|text=Jacob, when he was '''a''' dying}}
# {{lb|en|archaic}} ''To do with an action/movement;'' To, into. {{defdate|16th c.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} ''To do with method;'' In, with. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{RQ:Marlowe Jew of Malta|act=4|scene=3|text=Stands here '''a''' purpose.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} ''To do with role or capacity;'' In. {{defdate|from before 1150}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{ux-lite|en|[[a God's name|'''A''' God’s name]].}}

=====Usage notes=====
* {{sense-lite|position, direction}} Can also be attached without a hyphen, as [[aback]], [[ahorse]], [[afoot]]. See [[a-]]
* {{sense-lite|separation}} Can also be attached without hyphen, as [[asunder]]. See [[a-]]
* {{sense-lite|status}} Can also be attached without hyphen, as [[afloat]], [[awake]]. See [[a-]].
* {{sense-lite|process}} Can also be attached with or without hyphen, as [[a-changing]]

=====See also=====
* {{l-lite|en|on}}
* {{l-lite|en|a-}}

===Etymology 4===
From {{inh-lite|en|enm|a}}, {{m-lite|enm|ha}} contraction of {{m-lite|enm|have}}, or {{m-lite|enm|haven}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{l-lite|en|'a}}, {{l-lite|en|'a'}}, {{l-lite|en|ha}}, {{l-lite|en|ha'}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA-lite|en|/ə/}}
* {{rhymes-lite|en|ə|s=1}}

====Verb====
{{head-lite|en|verb forms|langname=English}}

# {{senseid|en|have}} {{lb|en|archaic|or|slang}} [[have|Have]]. {{defdate|between 1150 and 1350, continued in some use until 1650; used again after 1950}}<!--or earlier, but 1950 is the earliest I found offhand-->
#: {{ux-lite|en|I'd '''a''' come, if you'd '''a''' asked.}}
#: {{ux-lite|en|Oi'd '''a''' gen im a clout, if oi'd been theer.}} from Robert Holland, M.R.A.C., ''A Glossary of Words Used in the County of Chester,'' Part I--A to F., English Dialect Society, London, 1884, 1
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Hamlet|text=So would I '''a''' done by yonder ſunne<br/>?And thou hadſt not come to my bed.}}

=====Usage notes=====
* Now often attached to preceding auxiliary verb. See ''[[-a]]''.

=====Derived terms=====
