==Catalan==

===Etymology 1===

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA-lite|ca|/a/}}
* {{rhymes-lite|ca|a|s=1}}

====Letter====
{{head-lite|ca|letters|lower case||upper case|A|langname=Catalan}}

# {{Latn-def-lite|ca|letter|1|langname=Catalan}}

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l-lite|ca|no saber ni la a}}

=====See also=====
* [[Wiktionary:About Catalan#Letters|see other Catalan letters]]

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh-lite|ca|la|ad}}.

====Pronunciation====
* {{a|Eastern}} {{IPA-lite|ca|/ə/}}
* {{a|Western}} {{IPA-lite|ca|/a/}}

====Preposition====
{{head-lite|ca|prepositions|langname=Catalan}}

# [[in]], [[at]]; indicating a particular time or place
#: {{ux-lite|ca|Sóc '''a''' Barcelona.|I am '''in''' Barcelona.}}
# [[to]]; indicating movement towards a particular place
#: {{ux-lite|ca|Vaig '''a''' Barcelona.|I'm going '''to''' Barcelona.}}
# [[to]]; indicating a target or indirect object
#: {{ux-lite|ca|Escric una carta '''a''' la meva àvia.|I'm writing my grandmother a letter.}}
# [[per]]
# [[by]]
#: {{ux-lite|ca|dia '''a''' dia.|day by day.}}

=====Usage notes=====
When the preposition {{m-lite|ca||a}} is followed by a masculine definite article, {{m-lite|ca|el}} or {{m-lite|ca|els}}, it is contracted with it to the forms {{m-lite|ca|al}} and {{m-lite|ca|als}} respectively. If {{m-lite|ca||el}} would be elided to the form {{m-lite|ca|l'|l’}} because it is before a word beginning with a vowel, the elision to {{lang-lite|ca|[[a]] [[l’]]}} takes precedence over contracting to {{m-lite|ca|al}}.

The same occurs with the [[salat]] article {{m-lite|ca|es}}, to form {{m-lite|ca|as}} except where {{m-lite|ca||es}} would be elided to {{m-lite|ca|s’}}.

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l-lite|ca|al}}
* {{l-lite|ca|als}}
* {{l-lite|ca|as}}
* {{l-lite|ca|cap a}}
* {{l-lite|ca|per a}}

[[Category:ca:Latin letter names]]

