==Hawaiian==

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA-lite|haw|/aː/}}

===Conjunction===
{{head-lite|haw|conjunctions|langname=Hawaiian}}

# [[and]] (used between sentences)
# [[until]], [[up to]]

===Preposition===
{{head-lite|haw|prepositions|langname=Hawaiian}}

# [[of]], [[belonging]] to

====Usage notes====
* Used for acquired possessions, while {{m-lite|haw|o}} is used for possessions that are inherited, out of personal control, and for things that can be got into (houses, clothes, cars).

