==Latgalian==

===Etymology===
Ultimately from {{der|ltg|ine-bsl-pro|*ō}}. The source is not clear:
* Probably borrowed from a {{ncog-lite|sla|-}} language (compare {{ncog-lite|ru|а|tr=a|sc=Cyrl}} and {{ncog-lite|be|а|tr=a|sc=Cyrl}}). 
* Alternatively, irregularly shortened from {{lang-lite|ltg|*''ā''}}, inherited from {{m|ine-bsl-pro||*ō}}.
Compare {{ncog-lite|lt|o}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA-lite|ltg|/ˈa/}} <!-- {{ltg-IPA}} -->
* Hyphenation: {{lang-lite|ltg|a}} <!-- {{hyph|ltg|a}} -->

===Conjunction===
{{head-lite|ltg|conjunctions|g=f|langname=Latgalian}}

# [[and]], [[but]]

===References===
* {{R:ltg:Andronov:2008}}

