==Latvian==

===Etymology===
Proposed in 1908 as part of the new Latvian spelling by the scientific commission headed by [[w:Kārlis Mīlenbahs|K. Mīlenbahs]], which was accepted and began to be taught in schools in 1909. Prior to that, Latvian had been written in German [[Fraktur]], and sporadically in [[Cyrillic]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA-lite|lv|[a]}} <!-- {{lv-IPA|a}} -->
* {{audio|lv|lv-riga-a.ogg|Audio}}

===Letter===
[[File:Latin alphabet Aa.svg|thumb|upright=1.0|A]]
{{head-lite|lv|letters|lower case||upper case|A|langname=Latvian}}

# {{Latn-def-lite|lv|letter|1|langname=Latvian}}

====See also====
* {{list:Latin script letters/lv/simple}}

===Noun===
{{head-lite|lv|nouns|langname=Latvian|g=m|[[Appendix:Glossary#invariable|invariable]]||cat2=indeclinable nouns}} <!--{{lv-noun|m|-}}-->

# {{ng-lite|The name of the [[Appendix:Latin script|Latin script]] letter {{l-lite|lv|A}}/{{l-lite|lv|a}}.}}

====See also====
* {{list:Latin script letter names/lv/simple}}

===Further reading===
* {{pedia|lang=lv}}

