==Norwegian Bokmål==
[[Image:Latin letter A.svg|250px|thumb|The [[letter]]  '''''a''''' from the [[Norwegian]] alphabet.]]

===Etymology 1===
From {{der-lite|nb|la|a}}, from {{der-lite|nb|grc|-}} {{m-lite|grc|Α|sc=polytonic|tr=A|t=alpha}}, likely through the {{der-lite|nb|ett|-}} language, from {{der-lite|nb|phn|-}} {{m-lite|phn|langname=Phoenician|𐤀|tr=ʾ|sc=Phnx}}, from Proto-Canaanite [[Image:Protoalef.svg|20px]], from Proto-Sinaitic [[Image:Proto-semiticA-01.svg|20px]], from {{der-lite|nb|egy|-}} {{m-lite|egy|langname=Egyptian|sc=Egyp|𓃾}}, representing the head of an [[ox]].

====Pronunciation====
* {{sense-lite|letter name}} {{IPA-lite|nb|/ɑː/}}
* {{sense-lite|phoneme}} {{IPA-lite|nb|/ɑː/|/a/}}
