==Nupe==

===Etymology 1===

====Pronunciation====
* {{sense-lite|phoneme}} {{IPA-lite|nup|/a/|/ã/|qual2=after /n/ or /m/}}

====Letter====
{{head-lite|nup|letters|lower case||upper case|A|langname=Nupe}}

# {{Latn-def-lite|nup|letter|1|langname=Nupe}}

=====See also=====
* {{list:Latin script letters/nup}}

===Etymology 2===

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA-lite|nup|/à/}}

====Particle====
{{head-lite|nup|particles|head=à|langname=Nupe}}

# [[not]] {{gl|placed at the end of a clause to negate it}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|nup|Mi de eshìgi '''à''', mi ma de dàǹgi '''à'''.|I do'''n't''' have a dog, and I do'''n't''' have a cat.}}

===Etymology 3===
{{clipping|nup|lá}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA-lite|nup|/á/}}

====Particle====
{{head-lite|nup|particles|head=á|langname=Nupe}}

# {{ng-lite|Marks the [[perfective]] aspect, for actions that are completed}}

=====Usage notes=====
'''á''', which is derived from the verb {{m-lite|nup|la|lá|t=to take|langname=Nupe}}, functions like a verb so that the {{w|word order}} in the {{w|present perfect}} tense is that of a {{w|serial verb construction}}.

* {{ux-lite|inline=1|nup|Musa shi dùkùn|Musa bought a pot}}
* {{ux-lite|inline=1|nup|Musa '''á''' dùkùn shi.|Musa '''has''' bought a pot.|lit=Musa '''took''' a pot to buy}}

===Etymology 4===
{{clipping|nup|gà}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA-lite|nup|/à/}}

====Particle====
{{head-lite|nup|particles|head=à|langname=Nupe}}

# {{ng-lite|Used to express the [[future]] tense}} {{gl|placed before verbs}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|nup|A '''à''' lá èbi be nakàn|They '''will''' use a knife to cut the meat}}

----

