===Etymology 2===
From {{inh-lite|pt|roa-opt|a}}, from {{inh-lite|pt|la|illa}} (with the disappearance of an initial ''l''; compare {{cog-lite|es|la}}).

====Article====
{{pt-article}}

# {{senseid|pt|feminine definite article}} {{inflection of|pt|o||f|s|p=art}}
#* {{RQ:mul:Rowling Harry Potter|pt-BR|6|page=219|text=Então, como foi '''a''' última festinha de Slughorn?|t=So, how was the last Slughorn's little party?}}
#* {{RQ:mul:Rowling Harry Potter|pt-BR|7|page=147|text=Entregou '''a''' foto rasgada, [...]|t=He handed over the torn photograph, [...]}}

=====Quotations=====
{{seeCites|pt|o}}

=====See also=====
{{Portuguese articles}}

====Pronoun====
{{head-lite|pt|pronouns|g=f|third-person singular|langname=Portuguese}}

# {{senseid|pt|fsg direct objective pronoun}} [[her]], [[it]] (as a direct object; as an indirect object, see [[lhe]]; after prepositions, see [[ela]])
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Encontrei-'''a''' na rua.|t=I met her/it on the street.|inline=1}}

=====Usage notes=====
* Becomes {{m-lite|pt|la|-la}} after verb forms ending in ''-r, -s'', or ''-z'', the pronouns {{m-lite|pt|nos||us}} and {{m-lite|pt|vos||plural you}}, and the adverb {{m-lite|pt|eis||here is; behold}}; the final letter causing the change disappears.
*: After {{m-lite|pt|ver||to see}}: ''Posso vê-'''la'''?'' — “May I see '''her/it'''?”
*: After {{m-lite|pt|pôs||he/she/it put}}: ''Ele pô-'''la''' ali.'' — “He put '''her/it''' there.”
*: After {{m-lite|pt|fiz||I made; I did}}: ''Fi-'''la''' ficar contente.'' — “I made '''her/it''' become happy.”
*: After {{m-lite|pt|nos||us}}: ''Ela deu-no-'''la''' relutantemente.'' — “She gave '''her/it''' to us reluctantly.”
*: After {{m-lite|pt|eis||here is; behold}}: ''Ei-'''la'''!'' — “Behold '''her/it'''!”
* Becomes {{m-lite|pt|na|-na}} after a nasal vowel or diphthong: ''-ão, -am'' [ɐ̃w̃], ''-õe'' [õj̃], ''-em, -êm'' [ẽj̃].
*: ''Detêm-'''na''' como prisioneira.'' — “They detain '''her/it''' as a prisoner.”
* In informal Brazilian Portuguese, the nominative form {{m-lite|pt|ela||she}} is more commonly used.
*: ''Eu '''a''' vi.'' → ''Eu vi '''ela'''.'': “I saw '''her/it'''.”

=====Quotations=====
{{seeCites|pt}}

=====See also=====
{{see-temp|Portuguese personal pronouns|for more}}

===Etymology 3===
From {{inh-lite|pt|roa-opt|a}}, from {{inh-lite|pt|la|ad||to}} and {{m-lite|la|ab||from, away, by}}.

====Preposition====
{{head-lite|pt|prepositions|langname=Portuguese}}

# {{senseid|pt|introduces indirect object}} [[to]], ''introduces the indirect object''
#* {{RQ:mul:Rowling Harry Potter|pt-BR|6|page=143|text=Deixe-me mostrar '''a''' você...|t=Let me show it '''to''' you...}}
#* {{RQ:mul:Rowling Harry Potter|pt-BR|7|page=516|text=Não é bonito dizer isso '''a''' uma pessoa.|t=It's not nice to say that '''to''' a person.}}
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Dê-o '''a''' mim.|Give it '''to''' me.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Meu coração pertence '''a''' você.|My heart belongs '''to''' you.|inline=1}}
#: {{syn-lite|pt|para}}
# {{senseid|pt|indicates destination}} [[to]]; [[towards]], ''indicates destination''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Vamos '''a''' Paris!|Let’s go '''to''' Paris!|inline=1}}
#: {{syn-lite|pt|para|até}}
# {{senseid|pt|indicates physical distance}} [[away]], ''indicates a physical distance''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|A vila fica '''a''' onze milhas|The village is eleven miles '''away'''.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Comunicação '''à''' distância.|Communication '''at a''' distance.|inline=1}}
# {{senseid|pt|by means of}} [[with]]; [[by means of]], ''using as an instrument or means''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Mataram o cão '''a''' pauladas.|They bludgeoned the dog to death.|inline=1|lit=they killed the dog '''with''' bludgeonings}}
#: {{ux-lite|pt|'''A''' cavalo.|'''On''' horseback.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Livro escrito '''a''' lápis.|A book written '''with''' a pencil.|inline=1}}
#: {{syn-lite|pt|com|por meio de}}
# {{senseid|pt|using as a medium}} [[with]]; [[on]], ''using as a medium or fuel''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Quadro pintado '''a''' óleo.|A painting painted '''with''' oil.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Fornalha '''a''' carvão.|Coal furnace.|inline=1}}
# {{senseid|pt|in the specified measurement or quantity}} [[by]], ''using the specified measurement; in the specified quantity''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|É mais barato comprar comida '''ao''' quilo.|It is cheaper to by food '''by the''' kilogram.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Os fracassos ocorrem '''às''' dezenas.|Failures occur '''by the''' dozen.|inline=1}}
# {{senseid|pt|indicates steady progression}} {{lb|pt|preceded and followed by the same word}} [[by]], ''indicates a steady progression''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Calma lá. Resolva o problema passo '''a''' passo.|Easy there. Solve the problem step '''by''' step.|inline=1}}
#: {{syn-lite|pt|por}}
# {{senseid|pt|in the style or manner of}} ''in the style or manner of''; [[a la]]
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Ele puxou o temperamento '''ao''' pai.|He inherited his temperament '''from''' his father.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Camarão '''à''' grega.|Greek-'''style''' shrimp.|inline=1}}
#: {{syn-lite|pt|[[ao]] [[modo]] [[de]]}}
# {{senseid|pt|during the specified period}} {{lb|pt|limited use|see usage notes}} [[at]], ''during the specified period''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Dormimos '''à''' noite.|We sleep '''at''' night.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|pt|O filme começa '''às''' duas horas.|The film starts '''at''' two o’clock.|inline=1}}
#: {{syn-lite|pt|em|de}}
# {{senseid|pt|indicates location or position}} {{lb|pt|rare|_|except in set terms}} [[at]]; [[in]], ''indicates a location or position''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Isso fica '''à''' frente do altar.|This stays '''in''' front of the altar.|inline=1}}
#: {{syn-lite|pt|em}}
# {{senseid|pt|introduces the direct object emphatically}} ''indicates the direct object, mainly to avoid confusion when it, the subject, or both are displaced, or for emphasis''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|'''A''' mim ele não engana.|He doesn’t deceive me.|lit=To me he doesn’t deceive.|inline=1}}
# {{senseid|pt|forms the present participle}} {{lb|pt|Portugal|followed by a verb in the infinitive form}} ''forms the present participle; in Brazil, the gerund is used instead''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Estou '''a''' preparar a canja|I am prepar'''ing''' the chicken soup|inline=1}}
# {{senseid|pt|forms the future participle}} {{lb|pt|followed by an infinitive or present passive}} [[to]], ''forms the future participle''
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Um trabalho '''a''' ser feito.|A job '''to''' be done.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|pt|Nada '''a''' fazer.|Nothing '''to''' be done.|inline=1}}
#: {{syn-lite|pt|para|por}}

=====Usage notes=====
''When followed by a definite article'', '''a''' ''is combined with the article to give the following combined forms'':
* ''a'' + {{m-lite|pt|o}} → {{m-lite|pt|ao}}
* ''a'' + {{m-lite|pt|os}} → {{m-lite|pt|aos}}
* ''a'' + {{m-lite|pt|a}} → {{m-lite|pt|à}}
* ''a'' + {{m-lite|pt|as}} → {{m-lite|pt|às}}

In the sense of ''[[to]]'' (''introducing the indirect object'') usage with a personal pronoun can be replaced with an indirect pronoun ({{m-lite|pt|me}}, {{m-lite|pt|nos}}, {{m-lite|pt|te}}, {{m-lite|pt|vos}}, {{m-lite|pt|lhe}}, {{m-lite|pt|lhes}}):
* ''Deram um livro '''a ele'''.'' → ''Deram-'''lhe''' um livro.''

In the sense of ''[[at]]'' (''during the specified period'') it can be used with:
* {{m-lite|pt|noite||night}}
* {{m-lite|pt|noitinha||evening}}
* {{m-lite|pt|tarde||afternoon}}
* {{m-lite|pt|meio-dia||noon}}
* {{m-lite|pt|meia-noite||midnight}}
* specific hours

{{m-lite|pt|dia|Dia|day}}, {{m-lite|pt|manhã||morning}}, {{m-lite|pt|madrugada||early morning}} use {{m-lite|pt|de||of}} instead, which can optionally be used for ''tarde'', ''noitinha'' and ''noite'' as well. Names of months, days of the month and of the week use {{m-lite|pt|em||in}}.

