==Serbo-Croatian==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA-lite|sh|/a/}} <!-- {{sh-IPA|a}} -->

===Etymology 1===
See [[#Translingual|Translingual section]].

====Letter====
{{head-lite|sh|letters|lower case||upper case|A|langname=Serbo-Croatian}}

# The 1st letter of the Serbo-Croatian Latin alphabet ([[gajica]]), followed by {{l-lite|sh|b}}.

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|sh|sla-pro|*a|t=and, but}}.

====Conjunction====
{{sh-conjunction}}

# [[but]], [[and]] (compare {{m-lite|sh|ȁli}})
#: {{ux-lite|sh|učio sam c(ij)elo posl(ij)epodne, a ništa nisam naučio|t=I studied for the whole afternoon, but I didn't learn anything|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|sh|a kako biste vi to napravili?|t=and how would you do that?|inline=1}}
# [[while]] (on the contrary), [[whereas]]
#: {{ux-lite|sh|stolovi su crveni, a stolice su zelene|t=the tables are red, whereas the chairs are green|inline=1}}
# {{qual|with {{lang-lite|sh|[[da]] [[ne]]}}}} [[without]] (usually after negative verbs)
#: {{ux-lite|sh|ne mogu se uključiti u raspravu, a da ne napravim nered|t=I cannot enter a discussion without making a mess|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|sh|odlazi, a da nije rekao ni zbogom|t=he's leaving without even saying goodbye|inline=1}}
# ({{m-lite|sh||a}} {{m-lite|sh|ȉpāk}}) [[and]] [[yet]]
#: {{ux-lite|sh|pravi prijatelj zna sve o tebi, a ipak te voli|t=the real friend knows everything about you, and yet he loves you|inline=1}}
# ({{m-lite|sh||a}} {{m-lite|sh|kȁmoli}}) not to mention, [[let alone]]
#: {{ux-lite|sh|u moru loših v(ij)esti teško je ostati objektivan, a kamoli optimističan|t=in the sea of bad news it's hard to stay objective, let alone optimistic|inline=1}}
# ({{m-lite|sh||a}} + {{m-lite|sh|i}} + {{m-lite|sh|da}}) [[even if]]
#: {{ux-lite|sh|a i da jesam to napravio, ne bi to učinilo neku razliku|t=even if I did it, it wouldn't have made much of a difference|inline=1}}
# ({{m-lite|sh||a}} + {{m-lite|sh|i}}) and [[so]], and [[also]], and [[too]]
#: {{ux-lite|sh|sviđaju mi se plavuše, a i ja se pokojoj svidim|t=I like blondes, and some of them even like me|inline=1}}
#: {{ux-lite|sh|bili su žalosni, a i ja sam|t=they were sad, and so am I|inline=1}}

===Etymology 3===
Attested since the 15th century. Probably of onomatopoeic origin. Compare {{cog-lite|sl|a}}, {{cog-lite|ru|а|tr=a|sc=Cyrl}}, {{cog-lite|lt|o|õ}}, {{cog-lite|la|o|ō}} and {{cog-lite|grc|ὦ|tr=ô|sc=polytonic}}. These could all derive from Proto-Indo-European interjection {{m|ine-pro||*ō|oh, ah}}, but each form in individual languages could easily be an independent, expressive formation.

====Interjection====
{{head-lite|sh|interjections|Cyrillic spelling|а|f1sc=Cyrl|langname=Serbo-Croatian}}

# [[oh]], [[ah]]
#: {{ux-lite|sh|a da?|t=oh really?|inline=1}}

===References===
* {{R:sh:HJP|fQ%3D%3D}}
* {{R:sh:HJP|eg%3D%3D}}
* {{R:sh:Skok1971|vol=1|page=1}}

