===Etymology 4===
From the merge of {{inh-lite|scn|la|ad}} and {{m-lite|la|ab}}.

====Preposition====
{{head-lite|scn|prepositions|langname=Sicilian}}

# {{ng-lite|indicates the [[indirect object]]}}; [[to]]
#: {{ux-lite|scn|Porta stu panaru '''â''' nanna.|Bring this basket '''to''' grandma.}}
#: {{ux-lite|scn|'''Ê''' jatti ci piàciunu i pisci.|Cats like fish.|lit=Fish are pleasable '''to''' cats.}}
#: {{ux-lite|scn|E mû dumanni '''a''' mìa?|You're asking that '''to''' me?}}
# {{ng-lite|indicates the place, used in some contexts, in others {{m-lite|scn|in}} is used}}; [[in]], [[to]]
#: {{ux-lite|scn|Jemu '''â''' casa?|Can we go home?|lit=Can we go '''to the''' home?}}
#: {{ux-lite|scn|Cchiui staju '''a''' Palermu, '''a''' Ruma cci tornu dumani.|I'm '''in''' Palermo now, I'll go back '''to''' Rome tomorrow.}}
# {{senseid|scn|manner}} {{ng-lite|denotes the manner}}; [[with]]
#: {{lang-lite|scn|[[a pedi]], [[a muzzu]]}}
# {{ng-lite|denotes the direct object, but only if it's not preceded by articles}}
#: {{ux-lite|scn|Chiama '''a''' Paulu.|Call Paolo.}}
#: {{ux-lite|scn|E nun ni vidisti cchiui '''a''' nuiautri?|And you didn't see us?|footer=the "us" here is repeated twice for emphasis}}
#: {{ux-lite|scn|Ascutassi '''a''' mìa, signù!|Listen to me, ma'am!}}

=====Usage notes=====
* When followed by a word that begins with a vowel sound, the form {{m-lite|scn|ad}} (also rhotacized as {{m-lite|scn|ar}}) is used instead.
* When followed by the definite article, {{m-self|scn|a}} combines with the article to produce the following combined forms:
