==Slovene==
{{wikipedia|lang=sl}}

===Etymology 1===
From [[w:Gaj's Latin alphabet|Gaj's Latin alphabet]] {{m-lite|sh|a}}, from {{der-lite|sl|cs|-}} alphabet {{m-lite|cs|a}}, modification of capital {{m-lite|mul|A}}<!-- , itself derived from the {{der-lite|sl|ett|-}} letter {{m-lite|ett|𐌀|tr=a|sc=Ital}}, from the {{der-lite|sl|grc|-}} letter {{m-lite|grc|Α|tr=A|t=alpha|sc=polytonic}}, derived from the {{der-lite|sl|phn|-}} letter {{m-lite|phn|𐤀|t=ʾ|tr=[[aleph]]}}, from the {{der-lite|sl|egy|-}} hieroglyph {{m-lite|egy|𓃾|sc=Egyp}} -->.

====Pronunciation====
* {{q-lite|phoneme|tonal variety}}: {{IPA-lite|sl|/áː/|/àː/|/ʌ́/|/a/|[â]|[ǎ]}}
* {{q-lite|phoneme|non-tonal variety}}: {{IPA-lite|sl|/aː/|/a/}} <!--{{sl-IPA|aː|a}}-->
* {{q-lite|letter name}}: {{IPA-lite|sl|/àː/|/áː/}} <!--{{sl-IPA|ā}}-->
* {{audio|sl|Sl-nt-á.ogg|Audio (letter name, non-tonal)}}
