====Derived terms====
* {{l-self-lite|sl|a|à}}, {{l-self-lite|sl|a|á}}, {{l-self-lite|sl|a|ā}}, {{l-self-lite|sl|a|ȁ}}, {{l-self-lite|sl|a|ȃ}}
* {{l-lite|sl|ã}}, {{l-lite|sl|ȧ}}, {{l-lite|sl|ä}}, {{l-lite|sl|å}}, {{l-lite|sl|ḁ}}, {{l-lite|sl|ą}}
* {{l-lite|sl|če si rekel a, reci tudi b}}
* {{l-lite|sl|ena a}}
* {{l-lite|sl|od a do ž}}

===Etymology 2===
Attested since the 18th century. Probably of onomatopoeic origin. Compare {{cog-lite|sh|a}}, {{cog-lite|ru|а|tr=a|sc=Cyrl}}, {{cog-lite|lt|o|õ}}, {{cog-lite|la|o|ō}} and {{cog-lite|grc|ὦ|tr=ô|sc=polytonic}}. These could all derive from Proto-Indo-European interjection {{m|ine-pro||*ō|oh, ah}}, but each form in individual languages could easily be an independent, expressive formation.

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA-lite|sl|/àː/|/áː/|/á/}} <!--{{sl-IPA|ā|ȁ}}-->
* {{audio|sl|Sl-nt-á.ogg|Audio (non-tonal, long)}}
* {{audio|sl|Sl-nt-à.ogg|Audio (non-tonal, short)}}

* {{rhymes-lite|sl|aː}}
* {{homophones|sl|A|a}}

====Interjection====
{{head-lite|sl|interjections|langname=Slovene}} <!-- {{sl-interjection|-}} -->

