===Particle===
{{en-part}}

# {{non-gloss definition|A particle used for marking the following verb as an [[infinitive]].}}
#: {{ux|en|I want '''to''' leave.}}
#: {{ux|en|He asked me what '''to''' do.}}
#: {{ux|en|I have places '''to''' go and people '''to''' see.}}
#: {{ux|en|'''To''' err is human.}}
#: {{ux|en|Who am I '''to''' criticise? I've done worse things myself.}}
#* {{RQ:Pope Essay on Criticism|text='''To''' err, is human; '''to''' forgive, divine.}}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Hamlet|3|1|text='''To''' be, or not '''to''' be: that is the question: / {{...}}}}
#* '''2010''' July, [[w:Associated Press|Associated Press]], headline&nbsp;[https://web.archive.org/web/20100705003703/http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5gfMucgz8wUGUNUNXRyIyqzY6lWwQD9GM98N83]:
#*: Odds are, BP '''to''' get new CEO this year
#* {{quote-journal
|en
|date=April 10, 2011
|author=Alistair Magowan
|title=Aston Villa 1 - 0 Newcastle
|work=BBC Sport
|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_prem/9446263.stm
|page=
|passage=To that end, the home supporters were in good voice '''to''' begin with, but it was Newcastle who started the game in the ascendancy, with Barton putting a diving header over the top from Jose Enrique's cross.}}
# {{non-gloss definition|As above, with the verb implied.}}
#: {{ux|en|"Did you visit the museum?" "I wanted '''to''', but it was closed."}}
#: {{ux|en|If he hasn't read it yet, he ought '''to'''.}}
# {{non-gloss definition|Used to indicate an obligation on the part of, or a directive given to, the subject.}}
#: {{ux|en|You are '''to''' go to the store and buy a bottle of milk.}}
# {{lb|en|expressing purpose}} [[in order to|In order to]].
#: {{ux|en|I went to the shops '''to''' buy some bread.}}

