===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# {{lb|en|regionalism}} Toward a closed, touching or engaging position.
#: {{ux|en|Please push the door '''to'''.}}
#* {{RQ:Lawrence Sons and Lovers|[[s:Sons and Lovers/Chapter 12|chapter 12]]|text=He went in his room, pushed the door '''to''', without fastening the latch.}}
# {{lb|en|nautical}} Into the wind.
# {{misspelling of|en|too}}

====Usage notes====
The sense "toward a closed, touching or engaging position" is a regionalism found in various parts of the UK and US.

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|toward a closed, touching or engaging position}} {{l|en|closed}}, {{l|en|shut}}

====Antonyms====
* {{sense|toward a closed, touching or engaging position}} {{l|en|open}}, {{l|en|ajar}}

