==Danish==
{{cardinalbox|da|1|2|3|en|tre|ord=anden}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{der|da|non|tveir}}, from {{der|da|gem-pro|*twai}}, from {{der|da|ine-pro|*dwóh₁||two}}.

The modern Danish form is a merger of the original East Old Norse accusative masculine {{m|non|tvá|twā}} and the nominative/accusative feminine {{m|non|tvár|twāʀ}} (West {{m|non|tvær}}). The neuter {{m|non|tū}} (West {{m|non|tvau}}) is preserved in the adverb {{m|da|itu}}.

