==Emilian==

===Etymology===
From {{der|egl|la|inde|t=thence}}. Cognate with {{cog|ca|en}}, {{cog|fr|en}}, {{cog|it|ne}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA-lite|egl|/in/}}
* {{hyphenation|egl|in}}

===Pronoun===
{{head-lite|egl|pronouns|adverbial|langname=Emilian}}

# {{lb|egl|genitive case}} [[of]] [[it]], of [[them]]
#: {{ux-lite|egl|Vô-t di pām? A t’'''in''' dāg dû.|Do you want some apples? I will give you two ('''of them''').}}
# {{lb|egl|genitive case}} [[about]] [[it]], about [[them]]
#: {{ux-lite|egl|A t’'''in''' avîva descòurs ajêr.|I talked to you '''about it''' yesterday.}}
# {{lb|egl|ablative case}} [[from]] [[here]]
#: {{ux-lite|egl|A sòun stùf, a m’'''in''' vāg.|I am tired, I am leaving ('''from here''').}}

====Alternative forms====
* Becomes {{m-lite|egl|n-}} before a vowel (proclitic).
*: {{ux-lite|inline=1|egl|A-g '''n-'''ò dimándi.|I have a lot ('''of them''').}}
* Becomes {{m-lite|egl|-en}} when acting as an enclitic (after a consonant).
*: {{ux-lite|inline=1|egl|Mānj'''en''' un pōk!|Eat some '''of it'''! {{gloss|imperative, singular}}}}
* Becomes {{m-lite|egl|-n}} when acting as an enclitic (after a vowel).
*: {{ux-lite|inline=1|egl|Manjē'''n''' un pōk!|Eat some '''of it'''! {{gloss|imperative, plural }}}}

