==German==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA-lite|de|/ʔɪn/}}
* {{audio|de|DE-in.OGG|audio}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{der|de|goh|in}}, from {{der|de|gem-pro|*in}}.{{dercat|de|ine-pro|inh=1}}

====Preposition====
{{head-lite|de|prepositions|langname=German}}

# {{lb|de|with dative}} [[#English|in]], [[inside]], [[within]], [[at]] (inside a building)
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|Es ist '''in''' dem Haus.|It is '''in''' the house.}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|Ich habe die Schlüssel im ('''in''' dem) Kühlschrank gefunden.|I found the keys '''in''' the refrigerator.}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|Unsere Kinder sind '''in''' der Schule.|Our kids are '''at''' school.}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|Er ist '''in''' einem Café.|He is '''at''' a coffee shop.}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|Letzte Nacht waren sie im ('''in''' dem) Club.|They were '''at''' the club last night.}}
# {{lb|de|with dative}} [[#English|in]] {{gl|pertaining to}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|'''in''' diesem Sinne|'''in''' this/that sense}}
# {{lb|de|with dative}} [[#English|in]], [[at]], [[by]] (at the end of or during a period of time)
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|Er schloss sein Studium '''im''' Alter von vierzehn.|He completed his studies '''at/by''' the age of fourteen.}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|'''im''' Alter|'''in''' old age}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|im Mittelalter|'''during''' the middle ages}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|in den 1960er Jahren|'''in''' the 1960s}}
# {{lb|de|with accusative}} [[into]], [[to]] (going inside (of))
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|Er geht '''ins''' Haus.|He goes '''into the''' house.}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|Wir gehen '''in''' die Schweiz.|We are going '''to''' Switzerland.}}
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|de|Wir treten '''in''' ein neues Zeitalter ein.|We are coming '''into''' a new age.}}

=====Usage notes=====
The preposition ''in'' is used with the accusative case if the verb shows movement from one place to another, whereas it is used with the dative case if the verb shows location.

=====Derived terms=====
* ('''''in''' + dem'') [[im]] {{g|m|n}}
* ('''''in''' + das'') [[ins]] {{g|n}}
* {{l|de|in der Zwickmühle stecken}}

===Etymology 2===

====Contraction====
{{head-lite|de|contractions|langname=German}}

# {{lb|de|dated}} {{contraction of|de|[[in]] [[den]]}}

===Etymology 3===
{{bor+|de|en|in}}.

====Adjective====
{{de-adj|predonly}}

# [[#English|in]], [[popular]] (in fashion)

=====Declension=====
{{de-adecl|predonly}}

===Further reading===
* {{R:DWDS}}
* {{R:Kluge 1891}}

