==Latin==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alt|la|en|endo|indu||Old Latin}}

===Etymology===
From earlier {{m|la|en}}, from {{inh|la|itc-pro|*en}}, from {{inh|la|ine-pro|*h₁én|t=in}}. Cognate with {{cog|en|in}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{la-IPA|eccl=yes}}
* {{audio|la|la-cls-in.ogg|Audio (Classical)}}

===Preposition===
{{la-prep|ablative}}, {{la-prep|accusative}}

# {{lb|la|+ ablative}} [[#English|in]], [[at]], [[on]], [[upon]], [[from]] (space)
#* '''29 {{smallcaps|bc}}'''. [[w:Vergil|Vergil]]. ''[[w:Georgics|Georgics]]'', III
#*: {{smallcaps|omne adeo genvs '''in''' terris hominvmqve ferarvmqve}}<br/>{{smallcaps|et genvs æqvorevm pecvdes pictæqve volvcres}}<br/>{{smallcaps|in fvrias ignemqve rvvnt}}
#*:: So far does every species '''on''' earth of man and beast,<br/>whether the aquatic species, livestock, or painted-winged,<br/>collapse into the frenzies and the fire.
#* '''[[w:Seneca|Seneca]]'''
#*: {{smallcaps|venenum '''in''' auro bibitur}}
#*:: Poison is drunk '''from''' a gold cup.
# {{lb|la|+ ablative}} [[under]], [[within]], in
#* {{Q|la|Vergil|Eclogues|1|4|quote=lentus '''in''' umbrā|t=sluggish '''under''' the shade}}
# {{lb|la|+ ablative}} [[during]], [[within]], [[while]] in (time)
# {{lb|la|+ accusative}} [[into]], [[to]]
#* '''29 {{smallcaps|bc}}'''. [[w:Vergil|Vergil]]. ''[[w:Georgics|Georgics]]'', III
#*: {{smallcaps|omne adeo genvs in terris hominvmqve ferarvmqve}}<br/>{{smallcaps|et genvs æqvorevm pecvdes pictæqve volvcres}}<br/>{{smallcaps|'''in''' fvrias ignemqve rvvnt}}
#*:: So far does every species on earth of man and beast,<br/>whether the aquatic species, livestock, or painted-winged,<br/>collapse '''into''' the frenzies and the fire.
#* {{Q|la|Finnur Jónsson|Historia Ecclesiastica Islandiæ|1|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=6bwFAAAAQAAJ&lpg=PA313&ots=xwtdVF7_5p&dq=-Salvelinus%20-Crymostygius%20thingvallensis&pg=PA1#v=onepage&q&f=false|quote=De introductione religionis Christianæ '''in''' Islandiam.|trans=On the introduction of Christianity '''to''' Iceland.}}
# {{lb|la|+ accusative}} [[toward]], [[towards]], [[against]], [[at]]
#: {{ux-lite|inline=1|la|Gallī '''in''' Rōmānōs incurrunt.|The Gauls are rushing '''against''' the Romans.}}
#* {{Q|la|[[w:Titus Livius|Titus Livius]]|[[w:Ab Urbe Condita Libri|Ab Urbe Condita]]|I, 6|quote=Scelera '''in''' se fratris|t=The [[w:Amulius|brother’s]] crimes '''against''' [[w:Numitor|himself]]}}
#* {{Q|la|[[w:Titus Livius|Titus Livius]]|[[w:Ab Urbe Condita Libri|Ab Urbe Condita]]|I, 12|quote='''in''' {{l|la|adversum}} Romani {{l|la|subiere}}|t=The Romans marched '''against''' their enemy}}
# {{lb|la|+ accusative}} [[until]], [[for]]
# {{lb|la|+ accusative}} [[about]]
# {{lb|la|+ accusative}} [[according]] to
#* {{Q|la|[[w:Caesar|Caesar]]|[[w:de Bello Gallico|de Bello Gallico]]|VII, 19|quote=Generatimque distributi '''in''' civitates|t=and being distributed in tribes '''according to''' their respective nations}}

