==Middle English==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|enm|ang|inn}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{alt|enm|inn|inne|ine|yn|ynne}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA-lite|enm|/in/}}

====Noun====
{{enm-noun|pl=innes}}

# {{senseid|enm|inn}} Any kind of [[accommodation]]; particularly:
## A [[holiday]] [[home]] or [[guesthouse]]; a house set up as accommodation.
## An [[inn]] or [[hostel]]; a building with multiple rooms to let.
## A [[camp]] used by an army; [[barracks]].
# A [[home]] or [[house]]; [[habitation]] or [[housing]] one lives in.
# A [[dormitory]]; [[housing]] for [[students]].

=====Descendants=====
* {{desc|en|inn}}
* {{desc|sco|inn}}

=====References=====
* {{R:MED Online|entry=in |pos=n |id=MED22277 |accessdate=2018-05-02}}

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|enm|ang|in}}, from {{inh|enm|gem-pro|*in}}.{{dercat|enm|ine-pro|inh=1}}

====Alternative forms====
* {{alt|enm|ine|i|yn|yne|en|i|an|y}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA-lite|enm|/in/|/iː/|/i/|/ən/}}

====Preposition====
{{head-lite|enm|prepositions|langname=Middle English}}

# {{senseid|enm|in}} [[#English|in]]; with the following special senses:
## [[#English|in]], [[inside]]; [[encircled]] or [[confined]] by, with the following special senses:
### [[inside]], [[within]] {{gloss|a text or document}}
### [[inside]], [[within]] {{gloss|one's mind}}
### [[inside]], [[#English|in]], [[indoors]] [[of]].
### [[amongst]], [[#English|in]] a crowd of.
## [[wearing]], [[having]] [[on]], [[clad]] [[#English|in]]
## [[#English|in]] a [[quality]] or [[mode]]: with the following special senses:
### [[affected]] by, [[under]] the influence of.
### [[held]] by [[someone]], [[#English|in]] someone's [[grasp]]
### [[owned]] by [[someone]], [[#English|in]] someone's [[control]]
## [[inside]], [[at]] or [[on]] a [[location]] or [[place]].
## [[secured]] [[with]]; [[bound]] [[with]]
## [[#English|in]] the midst of, [[while]], [[currently]] [[doing]]
## [[#English|in]] (pieces or portions), [[into]].
## [[about]]; [[of]], [[on]] the [[matter]] of.
# [[#English|in]] the form, way, or manner of.
# [[on]], [[above]], [[on]] top [[of]].
# [[facing]] [[at]], [[#English|in]] the [[direction]] of.
# Being [[one]] of a set or group.
# Being owned by; in one's possession.
# [[due]] [[to]], [[as]], [[for]] the reason that.
# [[versus]]; in conflict with; fighting with.
# [[using]], [[utilising]], with the means of.
# {{lb|enm|rare}} [[with]], in the company of.

=====Usage notes=====
''in'' is usually [[postpositive]] in Middle English. For example, the previous sentence would be ''in is after þe noun lome Middel Englisch in''.

