==Old Irish==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|sga|cel-pro|*sindos||this}}, from {{inh|sga|ine-pro|*sḗm|t=one}} or {{m|ine-pro|*só|t=this}}; weak doublet of {{m|sga|sin|t=this}}.

====Article====
{{head-lite|sga|articles|langname=Old Irish}}

# [[the]] (masculine singular nominative/accusative; feminine singular accusative; masculine/feminine/neuter dual nominative/accusative/genitive)
#* {{RQ:sga-gloss|Wb|13|d|7}}
#*: Beóigidir '''in''' spirut '''in''' corp in ḟect so.
#*:: "The spirit now quickens the body."
# {{alternative spelling of|sga|ind}}
#* {{RQ:sga-gloss|Wb|13|d|7}}
#*: Beóigidir in spirut in corp '''in''' ḟect so.
#*:: "The spirit now quickens the body."

=====Usage notes=====
* Triggers nasalization of the following noun in the masculine and feminine singular accusative.
* Triggers lenition of the following noun as an alternative spelling of ''ind''.

=====Declension=====
{{sga-decl-in}}

=====Synonyms=====
* {{l|sga|int}} (masculine singular nominative, used before a vowel)

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|sga|insin}}
* {{l|sga|inso}}

=====Descendants=====
* {{desc|ga|an}}
* {{desc|gd|an}}
* {{desc|gv|yn}}

===Etymology 2===
{{rfe-lite|sga}}

====Particle====
{{head-lite|sga|particles|langname=Old Irish|triggers eclipsis}}

# {{non-gloss definition|interrogative particle forming yes-no questions}}

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|sga|duús in}}

====Verb====
{{head-lite|sga|verb forms|triggers eclipsis|langname=Old Irish}}

# {{infl of|sga|is||3|s|pres|indc|interrogative}}: is...?

===Etymology 3===

====Preposition====
{{head-lite|sga|prepositions|langname=Old Irish}}

# {{alt form|sga|i|t=in}} (often before {{m|sga|[[cach]], [[cech]]|t=each, every}} and {{m|sga|for|t=your {{g|p}}}})

===Etymology 4===
Probably originally the masculine/neuter dative singular of the definite article (see Etymology 1); compare {{cog|wlm|-}} and {{cog|cy|yn}}.<ref>{{R:sga:Thurneysen|pp=238–39|s=379}}</ref>

====Particle====
{{head-lite|sga|particles|langname=Old Irish}}

# {{n-g|Used with the masculine/neuter dative singular of an adjective to form the corresponding adverb}}: [[-ly]]
#* {{RQ:sga:Glosses|Ml|30|a|3}}
#*: {{quote|sga|Amal nád n-airigther ⁊ nád fintar a ndu·gníther hi suidi, {{m|la||sic}} ba '''in''' ḟortgidiu ⁊ ba hi temul du·gníth Saul cona muntair intleda ⁊ erelca fri Dauid.|As what is done in this is not perceived and discovered, so it was covertly and it was in darkness that Saul with his people was making snares and ambushes against David.}}

