===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/meɪk/|[meɪkʲ]}}
* {{audio|en|en-uk-to make.ogg|Audio (UK)}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-make.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|eɪk|s=1}}

===Etymology 1===
{{etymid|en|make}}
From {{der|en|enm|maken|sc=Latn}}, from {{der|en|ang|macian||to make, build, work}}, from {{der|en|gmw-pro|*makōn||to make, build, work}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*meh₂ǵ-||to knead, mix, make}}. Cognate with {{cog|la|mācerō}}, {{m|la|macer}}, {{cog|grc|μάσσω}}, {{cog|sco|mak||to make}}, {{cog|stq|moakje||to make}}, {{cog|fy|meitsje||to make}}, {{cog|nl|maken||to make}}, {{cog|nds-nl|maken||to make}} and {{cog|nds-de|maken||to make}}{{,}} and {{cog|de|machen||to make, do}}. Related to ''[[match]]''.

====Alternative forms====
* {{alter|en|mak||Wearside|Durham|dialectal}}
* {{alter|en|makee||pronunciation spelling}}
* {{alter|en|myek||Tyneside|dialectal}}

====Verb====
{{en-verb|makes|making|made|past2=maked|past2_qual=dialectal or obsolete}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[create]].
## To [[build]], [[construct]], [[produce]], or [[originate]].
##: {{syn|en|fabricate|Thesaurus:build}}
##: {{ux|en|We '''made''' a bird feeder for our yard.}}
##: {{ux|en|I'll '''make''' a man out of him yet.}}
##: {{ux|en|He '''makes''' deodorants.}}
##* {{RQ:Besant Ivory Gate|chapter=Prologue|passage=Thus, when he drew up instructions in lawyer language, he expressed the important words by an initial, a medial, or a final consonant, and '''made''' scratches for all the words between; his clerks, however, understood him very well.}}
##* {{quote-book|en|year=1913|author={{w|Joseph C. Lincoln}}|chapter=7|title=[http://openlibrary.org/works/OL5535161W Mr. Pratt's Patients]}}
##*: I '''made''' a speaking trumpet of my hands and commenced to whoop “Ahoy!” and “Hello!” at the top of my lungs. […] The Colonel woke up, and, after asking what in brimstone was the matter, opened his mouth and roared “Hi!” and “Hello!” like the bull of Bashan.
##* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-06-22|volume=407|issue=8841|page=68|magazine={{w|The Economist}}|title=[http://www.economist.com/news/finance-and-economics/21579860-g8-pledges-tackle-three-ts-t-time T time]}}
##*: Yet in “Through a Latte, Darkly”, a new study of how Starbucks has largely avoided paying tax in Britain, Edward Kleinbard{{...}}shows that current tax rules make it easy for all sorts of firms to generate what he calls “stateless income”:{{nb...}}. In Starbucks’s case, the firm has in effect turned the process of '''making''' an expensive cup of coffee into intellectual property.
## To [[write]] or [[compose]].
##: {{ux|en|I '''made''' a poem for her wedding.}}
##: {{ux|en|He '''made''' a will.}}
## To [[bring about]]; to [[effect]] or [[produce]] by means of some action.
##: {{ux|en|'''make''' war}}
##: {{ux|en|They were just a bunch of ne'er-do-wells who went around '''making''' trouble for honest men.}}
## {{lb|en|religious}} To [[create]] (the universe), especially {{lb|en|in Christianity}} from [[nothing]].
##: {{ux|en|God '''made''' earth and heaven.}}
## {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[prepare]] (food); to [[cook]] (food).
##: {{ux|en|I'm '''making''' cereal for breakfast. Who wants some?}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|now mostly|_|colloquial}} To [[behave]], to [[act]].
#: {{ux|en|To '''make''' like a deer caught in the headlights.}}
#: {{ux|en|They '''made''' nice together, as if their fight never happened.}}
#: {{ux|en|He '''made''' as if to punch him, but they both laughed and shook hands.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To tend; to contribute; to have effect; with ''for'' or ''against''.
#* '''1873''', {{w|Matthew Arnold}}, ''[[s:Literature and Dogma|Literature and Dogma]]''
#*: And all Israel's language about this power , except that it '''makes''' for righteousness , is approximate language
#* {{RQ:KJV|Romans|14|19|passage=Follow after the things which '''make''' for peace.}}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Henry 4-1|act=V|scene=i|passage=Considerations infinite / Do '''make''' against it.}}
# To [[constitute]].
#: {{ux|en|They '''make''' a cute couple.}}
#: {{ux|en|This '''makes''' the third infraction.}}
#: {{ux|en|[[one swallow does not a summer make|One swallow does not a summer '''make'''.]]}}
#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|chapter=5|passage=We '''made''' an odd party before the arrival of the Ten, particularly when the Celebrity dropped in for lunch or dinner. He could not be induced to remain permanently at Mohair because Miss Trevor was at Asquith, but he appropriated a Hempstead cart from the Mohair stables and made the trip sometimes twice in a day.}}
#* <!--should this be moved to a different sense? :
-->'''1995''', ''Harriette Simpson Arnow: Critical Essays on Her Work'', p.46:
#*: Style alone does not '''make''' a writer.
#* '''2014''', A teacher, "[http://www.theguardian.com/education/2014/sep/23/choosing-primary-school-guide-teachers-guide-for-parents Choosing a primary school: a teacher's guide for parents]", ''The Guardian'', 23 September:
#*: So if your prospective school is proudly displaying that "We Are Outstanding" banner on its perimeter fence, well, that is wonderful … but do bear in mind that in all likelihood it has been awarded for results in those two subjects, rather than for its delivery of a broad and balanced curriculum which brings out the best in every child. Which is, of course, what '''makes''' a great primary school.
