====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# [[brand|Brand]] or [[kind]]; [[model]].
#: ''What '''make''' of car do you drive?''
# [[manner|Manner]] or [[style]] of [[construction]] (style of how a thing is made); [[form]].
#* {{quote-book|en|1907|[[w:Mark Twain|Mark Twain]]|A Horse's Tale|url=http://www.gutenberg.org/dirs/etext97/hrstl10.txt
|passage=I can name the tribe every moccasin belongs to by the '''make''' of it.}}
# Origin (of a manufactured article); [[manufacture]]; [[production]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1905|author=[[w:Emma Orczy|Baroness Emmuska Orczy]]
|title=[[w:The Case of Miss Elliott|The Ayrsham Mystery]]
|chapter=2|url=http://openlibrary.org/works/OL8479084W
|passage=The cane was undoubtedly of foreign '''make''', for it had a solid silver ferrule at one end, which was not English hall–marked.}}
#* '''1914''', ''Judicious Advertising'', page 158:
#*: The Royal Typewriter Company is distributing a very attractive eight page folder, announcing the Royal Number 10, the first machine of Royal '''make''' which uses levers instead of wires to operate the type-bars.
#: ''The camera was of German '''make'''.''
# A person's [[character]] or [[disposition]].
