===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*gʰed-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|geten}}, from {{der|en|non|geta|}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*getaną}} (Cognate with {{cog|ang|ġietan}} (whence {{cog|en|yet}}), {{cog|goh|pigezzan|t=to uphold}}, {{cog|got|𐌱𐌹𐌲𐌹𐍄𐌰𐌽|t=to find, discover}}), from {{der|en|ine-pro|*gʰed-|t=to seize}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|gets|getting|got|got|past2=gat|past2_qual=archaic|past_ptc2=gotten|past_ptc2_qual=[[United States]], [[Canada]]|past_ptc3=getten|past_ptc3_qual=Geordie}}

# {{lb|en|ditransitive}} To [[obtain]]; to [[acquire]].
#: {{ux|en|I'm going to '''get''' a computer tomorrow from the discount store.}}
#: {{ux|en|Lance is going to '''get''' Mary a ring.}}
