==Limburgish==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alter|li|jett||Krefeld}}
* {{alter|li|gätt|gädd||Eupen}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|li|dum|iewet}}, {{m|dum|iet}}. The diphthong {{IPAchar|/ie̯/}} developed into {{IPAchar|/je/}} word-initially, as it did in [[High German]], and the onset was then enclitically hardened to ⟨g⟩ ({{IPAchar|/ʝ/}}). Cognate with {{cog|nl|iets}}, {{cog|gmw-cfr|jet}}, northern {{cog|lb|jett}}, {{m|lb|gett}}, {{cog|en|aught}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|li|/ʝæt/}}
* {{hyphenation|li|get}}
* {{rhymes|li|æt|s=1}}

===Adverb===
{{head|li|adverb}}

# [[some]], [[somewhat]]
# [[very]]
#: {{uxi|li|Ich woar mer '''get''' blij.|I was '''very''' happy.}}

===Pronoun===
{{head|li|pronouns|cat2=indefinite pronouns}}

# [[something]], [[anything]]
# {{lb|li|indefinite pronoun}} {{ngd|Placed before a plural noun, indicating general cases of people or things}}: [[some]]
#: {{uxi|li|Doe has '''get''' höng.|You own '''some''' dogs.}}

