# For each; [[per]].
#: {{ux|en|valued at half a pound '''the''' bushel; paying seven dollars '''the''' year interest}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1837|author={{w|James Edward Alexander}}|title=Narrative of a Voyage of Observation Among the Colonies of Western Africa, in the Flag-ship Thalia; and of a Campaign in Kaffir-land, on the Staff of the Commander-in-Chief, in 1835|city=London|publisher=Henry Colburn|volume=1|pages=251–2|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=GRZOAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA251|passage=Next morning I was up at an early hour, to see the market held near the water gate. The beef was excellent: but at the high prices of ten-pence and one shilling '''the''' pound; mutton at the same price; fowls a dollar '''the''' couple, and showing “more feathers than flesh.”}}
