==Old Saxon==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|osx|gem-pro|*sa}}. The original ''s-'' was replaced by ''th-'' by analogy with the other forms, but still preserved in the variant {{m|osx|sē}}.

====Determiner====
{{head|osx|determiner|cat2=demonstrative determiners|head=thē}}

# [[that]], [[that one]]
#: '''''them''' uuīha uuīsa lēstean'': To obey '''that''' holy wise.

=====Declension=====
{{osx-prondem|head=thē|the|that|thiu|thia|thana|that|thia|thia|thes|thes|thera|thero|themu|themu|theru|them|thiu}}

=====Descendants=====
* {{desc|gml|de}}
** {{desc|nds|de}}

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|osx|gem-pro|*þa}}, from {{inh|osx|ine-pro|*tó}}, {{m|ine-pro|*te-}}.

====Particle====
{{head|osx|particle|indeclinable, relative}}

# [[that]], [[who]], [[which]]

