==Catalan==

===Etymology 1===

====Pronunciation====
* {{ca-IPA|é}}
* {{rhymes|ca|e|s=1}}

====Noun====
{{ca-noun|f}}

# {{Latn-def|ca|name|B|b}}

=====Usage notes=====
In some dialects of Catalan, the sounds associated with the letter ''b'' and the letter ''v'' are the same: {{IPAchar|[b ~ β]}}. In order to differentiate ''be'' and {{m|ca|ve}} in those dialects, the letters are often called {{m|ca|be alta||high B}} and {{m|ca|ve baixa||low V}}.

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|ca|be alta}}

===Etymology 2===
Onomatopoeic from the sound of a lamb.

